
[1]glitter

   GLIT'TER, v.i.

   1. To shine; to sparkle with light; to gleam; to be splendid; as a
   glittering sword.

   The field yet glitters with the pomp of war.

   2. To be showing, specious or striking, and hence attractive; as the
   glittering scenes of a court.

    GLIT'TER, n. Brightness; brilliancy; splendor; luster; as the glitter
        of arms; the glitter of royal equipage; the glitter of dress.
     __________________________________________________________________

